  "comment": "Golden vectors for the lodestar-link object — GRAPH-SPEC Part A §5 (M4). The `canonical` vector is the load-bearing conformance case: an independent implementation MUST canonicalize these exact fields and compute this exact linkId (sha256 of the canonical form minus linkId, identical construction to recordId). Changing `expectedLinkId` is a format change and needs a DECISIONS entry. The `reject` cases pin verify-on-add: a link that is not well-formed, or whose id does not match its content, is refused with a stated verdict. Behavioral scenarios (retraction, same-repo merge, distinct suppression) are exercised in src/record/link.test.ts and src/graph/*.test.ts where dependent link ids can be minted.",
